:R-HSA-6793080  a           obo:GO_0000154 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Five modified nucleotides have been detected in the 12S rRNA: 5-methylcytidine-841 catalyzed by NSUN4, 6-dimethyladenosine-936 catalyzed by TFB1M, 6-dimethyladenosine-937 catalyzed by TFB1M, 5-methyluridine-429, and 4-methylcytidine-839 (reviewed in Van Haute et al. 2015). Four modified nucleotides have been detected in 16S rRNA: 2'-O-methylguanosine-1145 catalyzed by MRM1, 2'-O-methylguanosine-1370 catalyzed by RNMTL1 (MRM3), 2'-O-methyluridine-1369 catalyzed by FTSJ2 (MRM2), and pseudouridine-1397. 2'-O-methyluridine-1369 and 2'-O-methylguanosone-1370 occur in the A-loop of rRNA which is located at the peptidyl transferase center of the large subunit. Here the modified residues play a role in interaction with the aminoacyl site of tRNA. Knockouts of TFB1M and NSUN4 are lethal in mice and mutations in TFB1M may be related to aminoglycoside-induced deafness (reviewed in Van Haute et al. 2015)." ;
        rdfs:label          "rRNA modification in the mitochondrion" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: May, Bruce, 2015-08-28" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: May, Bruce, 2015-08-28" , "Reviewed: Bogenhagen, Daniel F, 2016-04-25" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-6793080" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-8868766/R-HSA-8868766> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

